title: Jacey Murphy
text:
Jacey Murphy (born March 21, 1989) is a Canadian <a href="rugby%20union">rugby union</a> player. She represented at the <a href="2014%20Women%27s%20Rugby%20World%20Cup">2014 Women's Rugby World Cup</a>, and <a href="2017%20Women%27s%20Rugby%20World%20Cup">2017 Women's Rugby World Cup</a>.
She made her debut at the <a href="Nations%20Cup%20%28Women%27s%20rugby%29%202013">2013 Nations Cup</a> against .
On July 2, 2019, nine months after giving birth to her first child, Grusnick played for Canada against France at the Super Series.
Murphy attended the <a href="University%20of%20Guelph">University of Guelph</a>. She works as an administrative assistant.
